<title>USA: S&amp;P puts American General on Creditwatch.</title>
<headline>S&amp;P puts American General on Creditwatch.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>Standard &amp; Poor's said on Tuesday it placed American General Corp's preferred securities offering and several issues of its debt on Creditwatch with negative implications.</p>
<p>American General's ratings continue remain on Creditwatch with negative implications, following the February 13, 1997 announcement of the company's planned $1.8 billion merger with USLIFE Corp, Standard &amp; Poor's said.</p>
